String are imutable in Java because if we are mutate an string 
in the java then its effect on the whole program;

Difference between String and String Builder;
1.
Using String Keyword we can directly create a string;String str="Satyam"
but if we want to create string using string builder 
then we need to first createe an object of String class after that using those object we can 
create string;
String str = new String("Satyam");

2. If you createe a String using String this will Store and maintain by Stringpool;
and if you createe a String using Stirng builder it will Store in Heap;

Method Of String;
 String str="Satyam"
 1.str.length()=this will give length of str;
 2.str.charAt(0)=this will give chreacter at 0 place;
 3.str.reverse()=this will reverse the string;
 4.str.substringOf(int i)=this will give sub string staritn form i to last;
 4.str.substringOf(int i,int j)=this will give sub string staritn form i to j;